body:
@simone-silvestri and I replaced a hardcoded `0.5` with `/2` as the former caused a type instability which eventually crashed the baroclinic adjustment setup after 13 days. How exactly that happened we don't know, but it definitely caused a cascade to Float64 - we believe even into the whole tendency - we shouldn't happen.

With this little change Float32 runs stable even with 9th order WENO V-scheme (velocities used for smoothness estimation when reconstructing vorticity) which is Simone's preferred scheme also for global simulations. 

Simone can you throw in the video and the kinetic energy comparison to Float64?
